Interests & Philosophy

“The future is not something we enter. The future is something we create.” Leonard Sweet

internet of things

the future is headed towards fridges which automatically tell you when you've run out of eggs, and mirrors which will beam up your day's agenda when you brush your teeth first thing in the morning. The internet will integrate into most of our physical world which is both incredible and scary!

design in nature's image

it's simply incredible to think that we have created computers in our own image, using the rules of nature. As tech is now rapidly evolving towards enhanced AI, it will be more important than ever to keep this design principle in mind, as we continue to model the new generations of computers after our own brain neural networks, or DNA code!

harness data

we live in a world where data is king- it is the oil of technoology which lubricates and allows better integration across applications. I strongly believe in using data responsibly, but also to create new insights! Big ups for API's!

positively contribute

whatever I choose to pursue I always believe in positive contribution - are my actions producing positive energies to the outside world or am I just doing something for myself? It can be both!

My Path

my career to date and where I want to go

  • 2011-2014

    OPEX Analyst @ Microsoft

    I was the lead OPEX analyst in central finance UK headquarters and maintained key financial rhythms and business partnering of a $20m OPEX fund. What I really loved though was developing cloud based power BI dashboarding suites and I decided to leave and refine my career direction towards programming (and do some travelling in between!)

  • 2016

    General Assembly - Web Development Immersive

    My curiosity for development led me to GA, where I attended the WDI course. This enabled me to gain a strong foundational understanding in Full Stack Web Development (see Technology section for detail) as well as developing industry standard practices such as AGILE workflow, TDD and Git version control.

  • 2016 - Future

    I want to continue my journey into code and am currently seeking opportunities in Full Stack Web Development. I've also started learning IoT development and am really interested in this space. Any organisations/startups which are involved with IoT development, Raspberry Pi/Arduino prototyping, data visualisation, green energies and horticulture are those which I am particularly interested in working for! Underlying that all, I strive to expand my knowledge base and am keen to contribute to code base.

Technology Stack

I feel most comfortable developing on a MEAN stack using JavaScript, however I can code in Ruby and have dabbled in Python too and am always up for learning new languages! I'm also starting to experiment with Internet of Things development - this is something I'm really interested in!
